description: Cybersyn's unique identifier for a state, joinable to GEOGRAPHY_INDEX.
Array of programs that were declared for the disaster to provide assistance.
The date a disaster was officially designated.
Unique record identifier from FEMA for a disaster and an associated impacted geography.

A unique code system FEMA uses internally to recognize locations that takes the numbers '99' + the 3-digit county FIPS code. There are some declared locations that dont have recognized FIPS county codes in which case a unique identifier is assigned.
The date the disaster areas were first entered into the NEMIS system.
Sequentially FEMA-assigned number used to designate an event or incident declared as a disaster.
The name or phrase describing the geographic area that was included in the declaration
Denotes that a declaration request was submitted directly to the President, independently of a state, by a Tribal Nation.
The official closeout date of a disaster, after which, one can no longer apply for assistance.
Cybersyn's unique identifier for a county, joinable to GEOGRAPHY_INDEX.
The date the disaster areas were last updated by NEMIS.
